  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Construction Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Site Management:</strong> Monitor daily construction activities, ensuring compliance with structural, safety, and building codes. Report to the sites early in the morning at 6 a.m. to make sure workers are at the client work sites on time and attend the TBM on daily basis.</li><li><strong>Safety Enforcement:</strong> Implement and enforce strict safety regulations, conducting regular inspections to identify and mitigate hazards.</li><li><strong>Team Leadership:</strong> Supervise, train, and schedule subcontractors and construction workers to meet project deadlines. Manage construction workers and make sure they reach on sites in a timely manner.</li><li>Need to visit the worker dormitories to ensure workers are staying in safe and healthy conditions.</li><li> Coordinate the timely delivery of materials, equipment, and tools to prevent workflow interruptions.</li><li> Inspect work for quality, verify adherence to blueprints and specifications, and provide regular progress reports to stakeholders. </li><li>Strong interpersonal skills for liaising with clients, engineers, and workers.</li><li>Good communication skills as need to manage workers from different countries.</li><li>Able to work in odd hours as and when required.</li><li>To be able to make purchases for the site related material as and when needed.</li><li>Ensure all authority-related requirements are followed during the execution of work and liaise with authorities if required.</li><li>Able to work under harsh and dusty environment.</li></ul>",
